Water supply might be affected when Rand Water workers affiliated to the South African Municipal Workers Union go on strike next week on Wednesday. Rand Water Spokesperson, Teboho Joala, reacts to this. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Water supply might be affected when Rand Water workers affiliated to the South African Municipal Workers Union go on strike next week on Wednesday. Rand Water supplies water to municipalities and industries in Gauteng, North West, Free State and Mpumalanga. WATCH: Strike at Rand Water averted, for now The union says the utility has failed to withdraw a circular informing workers they will no longer be receiving incentive bonuses.